For insurers acting as third-party investors:
  1. Investments in securitization exposures with long-term credit ratings of B or below, and in unrated exposures;
  2. Investments in securitization exposures with short- term credit ratings below S3, and in unrated exposures;
  3. Investments in securitization exposures for which the insurer has not met the due diligence requirements of section 5.2.
